# IFC Dashboard Architecture

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React (Vite), Three.js, `@thatopen/components` + `@thatopen/components-front`
- **Backend**: Python FastAPI (IFC parsing via `ifcopenshell`)
- **3D Engine**: That Open fragments (tile-based), PostproductionRenderer with SimpleRenderer fallback

## Project Structure

```
frontend/
  src/
    components/
      IfcViewer.jsx      — 3D viewer (That Open engine)
      Dashboard.jsx      — Charts and stats
      ElementTable.jsx   — Element data table
    contexts/
      SelectionContext.jsx — Shared state: selection, filters, isolation
    App.jsx              — Layout, file upload, routing
  public/
    Worker/worker.mjs    — FragmentsManager worker (copied from @thatopen/fragments)
    web-ifc.wasm         — WASM binary (copied from web-ifc)
    web-ifc-mt.wasm      — Multi-threaded WASM binary
backend/
  main.py                — FastAPI server, IFC parsing endpoint
TestIFC/                 — buildingSMART test files (IFC4, IFC4x3)
```

## Key Patterns

- **Bi-directional linking**: Dashboard click → `toggleFilter(expressIDs, label, key, globalIds)` → viewer isolates
- **Viewer click → Dashboard**: Highlighter event → GUID → `guidToExpress` map → `setSelectedExpressID`
- **Isolation modes**: highlight, isolate, xray (via Hider + Highlighter)
- **Context API**: `SelectionProvider` shares filter state across all components

## Dev Environment

- WASM files served from `public/` to avoid CDN/CORS issues
- FragmentsManager worker loaded as Blob URL
- No COOP/COEP headers (forces web-ifc single-thread, avoids worker path issues)
